JOHANNESBURG - Hartbeespoort Dam has yet again been invaded by water hyacinth, recently forcing the evacuation of a boat with 82 passengers and crew after it got entangled with the plants. Eyewitness News visited the dam to find out more about the impact of the water hyacinth, and how the issue is being resolved.  READ: PICS: Your sewage is contributing to Hartbeespoort Dam's alien hyacinth invasion